Ondo State Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, who is the Chairman of the sub-committee on Security and Compliance for the All Progressives Congress, APC, special convention for Presidential Primary, has guaranteed that the party’s primary poll will be free of hitches. Akeredolu, along by the committee’s co-chairman, Gen Abdulrahman Danbazau (Rtd), paid a visit to Eagle Square, the primary election’s location, to examine the degree of preparedness. The Governor stated that the party is prepared for the election, emphasizing that work on the venue, security, and other relevant operations has already begun. Akeredolu stated that the APC would have a trouble-free primary, stressing the party is a disciplined political party with disciplined members. “This is not our first time using this Eagle Square. We have knowledge of the venue already. No doubt, we are ready. “We have already started working on the venue, on security and everything. So, We are ready. I think we are good to go. “The APC is a disciplined party. We are going to have a hitch-free primary. We are a disciplined party and our members will show discipline here on the D-day.”